17
00:02:00,320 --> 00:02:02,500
What's wrong with you today? Why are you eating so little?

18
00:02:02,500 --> 00:02:04,260
Does it taste bad, or does your stomach hurt?

19
00:02:04,260 --> 00:02:09,520
No. I had some bread before evening study, so I'm not too hungry.

20
00:02:11,560 --> 00:02:13,910
If you don't want to eat, forget it.

21
00:02:14,518 --> 00:02:15,780
I'll put it away.

22
00:02:15,780 --> 00:02:17,510
Mom, let me put it away.

23
00:02:17,510 --> 00:02:19,220
Let me do it.

24
00:02:20,180 --> 00:02:23,620
You're really thoughtful.

25
00:02:35,960 --> 00:02:39,580
What are you doing? You're walking so slowly. Hurry up. Walk.

26
00:02:44,200 --> 00:02:46,240
Mr. Song,

27
00:02:47,016 --> 00:02:49,361
why aren't the lights on at night?

28
00:02:49,361 --> 00:02:51,581
I just got them working.

29
00:02:55,897 --> 00:02:57,331
What are you standing there for, Chen Huan Er?

30
00:02:57,331 --> 00:02:58,711
Come here.

31
00:03:01,260 --> 00:03:04,400
Let me introduce you. This is the puppy from our compound.

32
00:03:04,400 --> 00:03:07,520
It's called Little Bro. But since you're here, you're the new Little Bro.

33
00:03:07,520 --> 00:03:09,000
Sit.

34
00:03:29,000 --> 00:03:31,677
What are you waiting for? Eat.

35
00:03:32,280 --> 00:03:36,184
Let me tell you. Aunt Hao is the best cook in our compound.

36
00:03:36,184 --> 00:03:38,271
Since I was little, I've looked forward to my mom working overtime

37
00:03:38,271 --> 00:03:41,540
so she could send me to their house for a free meal.

38
00:03:44,460 --> 00:03:47,320
I'm really sorry.

39
00:03:47,320 --> 00:03:49,650
- I'm troubling— 
 - Don't mention it.

40
00:03:49,650 --> 00:03:55,080
Let me tell you. Mr. Song gave me extra food because he saw how hard I trained.

41
00:03:55,080 --> 00:03:57,780
Are you going to eat it? I'll eat it if you don't.

42
00:03:57,780 --> 00:04:00,350
What are you talking about? Let her eat first.

43
00:04:00,350 --> 00:04:03,340
- Hurry. 
 - Thank you.

44
00:04:09,280 --> 00:04:10,910
It's good, right?

45
00:04:11,920 --> 00:04:14,510
- It's good. 
 - I'll try it too.

46
00:04:14,510 --> 00:04:16,360
I'm telling you,

47
00:04:16,360 --> 00:04:19,520
this secret hideout is our masterpiece.

48
00:04:19,520 --> 00:04:26,650
None of the parents in the compound ever figured out that we set it up

49
00:04:26,650 --> 00:04:30,170
right along their daily commute route.

50
00:04:31,065 --> 00:04:32,550
Song Cong.

51
00:04:32,550 --> 00:04:34,120
 Song Cong? 

52
00:04:34,120 --> 00:04:37,020
Bring two more dishes to Huan Er.

53
00:04:40,250 --> 00:04:41,720
Coming.

54
00:04:59,300 --> 00:05:01,720
 Mom. 

55
00:05:01,720 --> 00:05:05,340
 Mom. 

56
00:05:09,010 --> 00:05:12,500
So, is this where you saw me that day?

57
00:05:12,500 --> 00:05:13,910
Yes.

58
00:05:13,910 --> 00:05:18,110
But rest assured, I won't tell anyone about it.

59
00:05:19,740 --> 00:05:22,030
I didn't cry that day.

60
00:05:22,030 --> 00:05:24,030
I understand.

61
00:05:24,030 --> 00:05:27,620
Girls are self-conscious.

62
00:05:27,620 --> 00:05:28,910
But don't worry.

63
00:05:28,910 --> 00:05:33,550
Only heaven, earth, you, and I know you cried because of your exam.

64
00:05:33,550 --> 00:05:36,910
- No third person will know about it. 
 - Enough.

65
00:05:36,910 --> 00:05:39,960
Stop talking about Huan Er's crying.

66
00:05:39,960 --> 00:05:43,520
No fourth person will know. Rest assured.

67
00:05:43,520 --> 00:05:44,840
Really.

68
00:05:44,840 --> 00:05:46,910
I really didn't cry.

69
00:05:46,910 --> 00:05:48,160
You didn't cry.

70
00:05:48,160 --> 00:05:49,940
- She said she didn't cry. 
 - You don't believe?

71
00:05:49,940 --> 00:05:51,720
- I believe you. 
 - You didn't cry.

72
00:05:51,720 --> 00:05:53,000
Here, have a sip.

73
00:05:53,000 --> 00:05:55,700
- My mom's heavy-handed with seasoning. 
 - Thank you.

74
00:06:02,820 --> 00:06:07,150
There are so many dishes. I can't finish them.

75
00:06:07,150 --> 00:06:08,960
You don't have to be so polite.

76
00:06:08,960 --> 00:06:11,211
Everyone in this compound knows each other.

77
00:06:11,211 --> 00:06:16,883
Going to someone else's house for a meal is like our parents working shifts.

78
00:06:16,883 --> 00:06:20,409
Now that you're here, you have to go with the flow.

79
00:06:20,409 --> 00:06:24,499
You should quickly adapt and join us.

80
00:06:25,260 --> 00:06:30,350
Next time when Aunt Li Na is on duty, come to my house for a meal.

81
00:06:31,050 --> 00:06:34,600
If you refuse again, my mom will be angry.

82
00:06:39,180 --> 00:06:40,710
Fine.

83
00:06:40,710 --> 00:06:46,160
I'll adapt and try hard to keep up.

84
00:06:46,160 --> 00:06:50,590
If you need us in the future, text us "Secret Base"

85
00:06:50,590 --> 00:06:54,010
and we'll know you want to meet here in ten minutes.

86
00:06:54,010 --> 00:06:55,690
Okay.

87
00:06:56,720 --> 00:06:58,200
Great.

88
00:06:58,200 --> 00:06:59,520
We're finally a trio again.

89
00:06:59,520 --> 00:07:01,960
What do you mean, "a trio again"?

90
00:07:01,960 --> 00:07:03,770
Do you want to know?

91
00:07:05,110 --> 00:07:06,940
Lend me your homework for a week, and I'll tell you.

92
00:07:06,940 --> 00:07:09,280
Stop being mysterious. Just tell me.

93
00:07:09,280 --> 00:07:11,200
It's Li Tian.

94
00:07:12,120 --> 00:07:14,313
Li Tian?

95
00:07:14,313 --> 00:07:16,820
Let's not talk about him. Let's eat.

96
00:07:18,300 --> 00:07:19,940
Go away.

97
00:07:19,940 --> 00:07:21,940
Why didn't you bring him some food?

98
00:07:21,940 --> 00:07:23,840
He eats a lot every day.

99
00:07:23,840 --> 00:07:25,550
Here. Call him your senior.

100
00:07:25,550 --> 00:07:27,260
I'm not his junior.

101
00:07:27,260 --> 00:07:29,520
- I'm the boss. He's your senior. 
 - Don't talk so much.

102
00:07:29,520 --> 00:07:31,960
Here, look at her. She's your junior. Your new junior.

103
00:07:31,960 --> 00:07:34,354
Chen Huan Er is your new little bro.

104
00:07:34,354 --> 00:07:36,640
Does he need to be renamed? You don't even acknowledge him anymore?

105
00:07:36,640 --> 00:07:38,060
What shall we name him then?

106
00:07:38,060 --> 00:07:40,680
Call him Second Brother. You're Little Brother.

107
00:07:55,920 --> 00:07:59,160
Song Cong, get up!

108
00:08:00,150 --> 00:08:01,990
Huan Er.

109
00:08:01,990 --> 00:08:04,380
I'm late. I need to rush to work.

110
00:08:04,380 --> 00:08:06,500
You hurry up.

111
00:08:06,500 --> 00:08:08,480
Got it.

112
00:08:24,940 --> 00:08:26,740
Morning.

113
00:08:26,740 --> 00:08:28,500
You didn't have breakfast, right?

114
00:08:28,500 --> 00:08:30,280
My mom made it.

115
00:08:30,280 --> 00:08:32,180
Is it for me?

116
00:08:33,407 --> 00:08:35,617
Thank you.

117
00:08:41,990 --> 00:08:45,260
Cherish it. It's my mom's turn tomorrow.

118
00:08:50,760 --> 00:08:54,470
 Living in a family housing compound finally shows its advantages. 

119
00:08:54,470 --> 00:08:57,950
 You'll never go hungry. 

120
00:08:57,950 --> 00:09:00,540
 I'm not afraid of how busy Mom is at the hospital. 

121
00:09:00,540 --> 00:09:03,810
 The families will help each other. 

122
00:09:05,880 --> 00:09:11,480
 As for cooking skills, everyone is different. 

123
00:09:14,360 --> 00:09:16,935
Are you really eating it? I gave you some, and you really ate it!

124
00:09:16,935 --> 00:09:19,160
What am I going to eat if you ate it?

125
00:09:20,000 --> 00:09:21,680
Don't follow me.

126
00:09:28,990 --> 00:09:34,430
 Our vegetable buns still haven't received the family's approval. 

127
00:09:34,430 --> 00:09:36,740
When is Aunt Hao's day off?

128
00:09:37,260 --> 00:09:39,260
If you don't like it, don't eat it.

129
00:09:39,260 --> 00:09:43,070
   

130
00:09:44,440 --> 00:09:46,190
I heard Song Cong turned in his paper early that day

131
00:09:46,190 --> 00:09:47,940
so he could finish school with Ms. Kaosign.

132
00:09:47,940 --> 00:09:50,840
- Are they really— 
 - Stop talking.

133
00:10:03,360 --> 00:10:08,570
Huan Er, is there something going on between you and Song Cong?

134
00:10:08,570 --> 00:10:11,500
You believe it too?

135
00:10:11,500 --> 00:10:14,480
People who don't know the truth might actually believe it.

136
00:10:14,480 --> 00:10:15,900
Nothing is going on.

137
00:10:15,900 --> 00:10:19,500
   

138
00:10:28,480 --> 00:10:30,680
You improved so much on this test. 
    

139
00:10:30,680 --> 00:10:33,220
Is it because Song Cong tutored you?

140
00:10:38,040 --> 00:10:40,500
Then can I sit in on the lessons too?

141
00:10:40,500 --> 00:10:44,430
Sure. I'll talk to Song Cong.

142
00:10:44,430 --> 00:10:46,600
Stand up!

143
00:10:47,230 --> 00:10:50,590
 Hello, Sir. 

144
00:10:50,590 --> 00:10:51,909
Hello, students.

145
00:10:51,909 --> 00:10:59,909
   

146
00:11:05,140 --> 00:11:09,160
Cong, are these leftover bottles from infusions?

147
00:11:10,260 --> 00:11:12,620
Empty saline bottles.

148
00:11:12,620 --> 00:11:19,390
They're my dad's invention, but I think it's no different from watering plants directly.

149
00:11:21,680 --> 00:11:24,500
Cong, after we're done eating, come to our house to play.

150
00:11:24,500 --> 00:11:27,760
No. I have to tutor Huan Er later.

151
00:11:29,350 --> 00:11:31,240
Tutoring on weekends?

152
00:11:31,240 --> 00:11:33,454
I asked you to play football last week, but you had tutoring.

153
00:11:33,454 --> 00:11:36,530
I asked you to go to the base before, but you were tutoring.

154
00:11:36,530 --> 00:11:39,060
You too... you come here for tutoring every week.

155
00:11:39,060 --> 00:11:41,850
You even freeload meals. Don't you think it's too far?

156
00:11:41,850 --> 00:11:43,940
What's too far? We're all in the same compound.

157
00:11:43,940 --> 00:11:46,210
Huan Er, eat it while it's hot.

158
00:11:46,210 --> 00:11:47,620
Thank you.

159
00:11:47,620 --> 00:11:51,160
As for you, I've never seen you be so proactive when studying.

160
00:11:51,160 --> 00:11:53,480
When it comes to mealtime, you're more punctual than others.

161
00:11:53,480 --> 00:11:56,710
Aunt Hao, I went to play football, and it's also a serious matter.

162
00:11:56,710 --> 00:11:58,160
Your mother just told me today.

163
00:11:58,160 --> 00:12:01,540
Even if you're a special student, you can't fall behind in your studies.

164
00:12:01,540 --> 00:12:04,520
I... Yes. I'll stop talking. I'll eat, alright?

165
00:12:04,520 --> 00:12:07,260
- I'll eat. 
 - Aunt Hao, your cooking is delicious.

166
00:12:07,260 --> 00:12:08,710
Much better than my mom's.

167
00:12:08,710 --> 00:12:11,830
Really? Eat more.

168
00:12:14,380 --> 00:12:17,090
Chen Huan Er, you're a bit shameless now.

169
00:12:17,090 --> 00:12:18,760
I'll tell your mom later.

170
00:12:18,760 --> 00:12:21,440
- You wouldn't dare. 
 - Didn't you flatter me before by saying

171
00:12:21,440 --> 00:12:22,872
that my mom is the best cook in the compound?

172
00:12:22,872 --> 00:12:26,130
No. Why are you all siding with her?

173
00:12:26,130 --> 00:12:29,330
Chen Huan Er, let's do this one-on-one. Don't seek outside help.

174
00:12:29,330 --> 00:12:30,520
What one-on-one?

175
00:12:30,520 --> 00:12:32,610
Say it in English.

176
00:12:32,610 --> 00:12:34,890
Can you make it more international?

177
00:12:34,890 --> 00:12:36,010
Your English has improved.

178
00:12:36,010 --> 00:12:37,660
- Yes. 
 - You're no longer Ms. Kaosign?

179
00:12:37,660 --> 00:12:40,360
Fine. Let me drink some water to calm down.

180
00:12:40,360 --> 00:12:42,340
That's my water.

181
00:12:43,800 --> 00:12:45,180
I know it's yours.

182
00:12:45,180 --> 00:12:46,600
Why did you drink it if you knew?

183
00:12:46,600 --> 00:12:47,900
Stop being dramatic!

184
00:12:47,900 --> 00:12:49,937
Everyone here shares their water.

185
00:12:49,937 --> 00:12:51,220
What's wrong with drinking your water?

186
00:12:51,220 --> 00:12:52,510
You have oil all over your hand.

187
00:12:52,510 --> 00:12:54,380
- Wash it. 
 - I won't. 
 - Wash it.

188
00:12:54,380 --> 00:12:55,780
Whoever drank first should do the dishes.

189
00:12:55,780 --> 00:12:57,020
- Didn't you drink it? 
 - I'm not doing it.

190
00:12:57,020 --> 00:12:58,430
Why did you break the rules?

191
00:12:58,430 --> 00:12:59,320
- Do it. 
 - What's wrong?

192
00:12:59,320 --> 00:13:00,700
I'm not washing them.

193
00:13:00,700 --> 00:13:02,110
I'm not washing them today!

194
00:13:02,110 --> 00:13:03,080
- Just do it! 
 - Ouch!

195
00:13:03,080 --> 00:13:04,190
- Are you doing it or not? 
 - Ouch!

196
00:13:04,190 --> 00:13:06,720
My arm hurts. Cong!

197
00:13:06,720 --> 00:13:08,360
Look, she's hurting my elbow.

198
00:13:08,360 --> 00:13:10,109
I'm in pain. She hurt me like this.

199
00:13:10,109 --> 00:13:11,989
- I can't move. Look. 
 - Enough.

200
00:13:11,989 --> 00:13:14,389
Cong, look, I can't move it.

201
00:13:14,389 --> 00:13:16,600
Be the judge here. How can she do this?

202
00:13:16,600 --> 00:13:19,140
She'll become the boss here soon. Look.

203
00:13:19,140 --> 00:13:20,800
Qi Qi should be here.

204
00:13:20,800 --> 00:13:22,680
I'm going to pick up Qi Qi.

205
00:13:22,680 --> 00:13:25,919
Cong, I'll go downstairs first. Open the door for me in a moment.

206
00:13:29,623 --> 00:13:31,263
Qi Qi?

207
00:13:32,515 --> 00:13:34,427
Is she coming for your tutorials?

208
00:13:35,243 --> 00:13:38,553
- Yeah. 
 - Why didn't you say so earlier?

209
00:13:38,553 --> 00:13:41,073
You didn't ask.

210
00:14:10,820 --> 00:14:13,240
 What are you doing here? 

211
00:14:14,833 --> 00:14:17,603
Studying, of course.

212
00:14:18,700 --> 00:14:20,296
What are you looking at?

213
00:14:20,296 --> 00:14:23,720
Even though you've made progress, can't I stop being the last in class?

214
00:14:23,720 --> 00:14:25,770
You have a goal now.

215
00:14:27,163 --> 00:14:29,400
Studying is a good thing.

216
00:14:29,400 --> 00:14:31,920
It's good that everyone is together.

217
00:14:31,920 --> 00:14:33,400
Qi Qi.

218
00:14:33,400 --> 00:14:36,474
I bought some oranges. I don't know if you like them.

219
00:14:36,474 --> 00:14:38,560
- Thank you, Aunt. 
 - Don't mention it.

220
00:14:38,560 --> 00:14:40,593
- Song Cong, there's more. Cut more if it's not enough. 
 - Okay.

221
00:14:40,593 --> 00:14:43,013
Don't exhaust yourselves with studying. Take a break later.

222
00:14:43,013 --> 00:14:44,853
- I'm going to go. 
 - Bye.

223
00:14:44,853 --> 00:14:46,923
- Bye, Aunt Hao. 
 - Bye.

224
00:14:46,923 --> 00:14:49,333
She's so nice.

225
00:14:51,613 --> 00:14:54,243
Did she go out because of me?

226
00:14:54,243 --> 00:14:57,163
I'm so sorry to bother you.

227
00:14:57,163 --> 00:15:01,323
Don't overthink it. My mom is in a hurry to play mahjong.

228
00:15:01,920 --> 00:15:05,523
Well, Aunt Hao, my mom, her mom, and Li Tian's mom

229
00:15:05,523 --> 00:15:08,010
make the perfect four-player set.

230
00:15:08,763 --> 00:15:10,433
Do all your parents know each other?

231
00:15:10,433 --> 00:15:13,893
Of course. Every parent in this compound knows each other.

232
00:15:13,893 --> 00:15:15,860
Li Tian from our class lives upstairs.

233
00:15:15,860 --> 00:15:19,043
We've known each other since we were in diapers.

234
00:15:19,043 --> 00:15:23,750
In that case, why don't you ever go to school with Li Tian?

235
00:15:24,413 --> 00:15:26,123
Because...

236
00:15:26,123 --> 00:15:30,480
That's because he's Dr. Li's son.

237
00:15:30,480 --> 00:15:32,360
 You even answered such a question wrong. 

238
00:15:32,360 --> 00:15:34,833
 Did you even read it? 

239
00:15:34,833 --> 00:15:37,793
 Because of this mistake, you didn't get a perfect score. 

240
00:15:37,793 --> 00:15:40,983
 Aren't you embarrassed? I'm embarrassed for you. 

241
00:15:41,800 --> 00:15:49,143
 Tian, although you're number one in class, do you know that Song Cong got full marks? 

242
00:15:49,893 --> 00:15:51,283
 Tian. 

243
00:15:51,283 --> 00:15:55,513
 You must work hard. You know your father has high expectations of you. 

244
00:16:03,860 --> 00:16:05,123
 Here's some gossip. 

245
00:16:05,123 --> 00:16:09,187
 Yesterday, Mrs. Li scolded her son. Did you know that? 

246
00:16:09,187 --> 00:16:13,165
 I'm telling you, Li Tian's mom scolded Li Tian again. 

247
00:16:13,165 --> 00:16:15,285
 This kid is unfortunate. 

248
00:16:22,533 --> 00:16:24,393
 I'm dying of laughter. 

249
00:16:24,393 --> 00:16:27,283
Your family housing compound is really interesting.

250
00:16:28,163 --> 00:16:29,553
All right, enough. Let's study.

251
00:16:29,553 --> 00:16:31,120
- Sure. 
 - Okay.

252
00:16:31,120 --> 00:16:35,320
Song Cong, remember the problem you explained last time? This one.

253
00:16:35,320 --> 00:16:38,632
I haven't figured it out yet. Can you explain it again?

