Aunt Hao already planned it for him.

513
00:31:33,000 --> 00:31:34,058
What plan?

514
00:31:34,058 --> 00:31:35,981
He's going abroad. Is there any need to say more?

515
00:31:35,981 --> 00:31:39,640
From participating in competitions and winning awards to applying to prestigious schools.

516
00:31:39,640 --> 00:31:42,920
He's different from us. He's going to do great things.

517
00:31:43,677 --> 00:31:46,820
It sounds so tiring.

518
00:31:46,820 --> 00:31:51,640
Will such a planned life make you happy?

519
00:31:57,670 --> 00:31:59,360
No, I mean...

520
00:31:59,920 --> 00:32:02,999
When I was young, my grandpa took me to the mountains to dig herbs.

521
00:32:02,999 --> 00:32:07,050
He told me the most amazing thing about plants is that they have no heart.

522
00:32:07,050 --> 00:32:12,440
Because they have no feelings or emotions, they survive only by natural instincts.

523
00:32:12,440 --> 00:32:14,390
But humans are different.

524
00:32:14,390 --> 00:32:18,870
Don't people live to be happy?

525
00:32:22,280 --> 00:32:24,770
Don't say so much. What is he unhappy about?

526
00:32:24,770 --> 00:32:27,020
He's a top student.

527
00:32:27,020 --> 00:32:28,420
Why are you so proud of that?

528
00:32:28,420 --> 00:32:29,440
Aren't you jealous?

529
00:32:29,440 --> 00:32:31,850
Jealous of what? I'm not Li Tian.

530
00:32:31,850 --> 00:32:35,570
Besides, do you think I'm just anyone?

531
00:32:35,570 --> 00:32:37,260
If you want to see me in the future,

532
00:32:37,260 --> 00:32:42,320
you have to make an appointment with my club, Real Madrid, six months in advance.

533
00:32:42,320 --> 00:32:45,157
All right, hurry up, or we won't be able to finish this.

534
00:32:45,157 --> 00:32:47,100
You don't believe me?

535
00:32:47,100 --> 00:32:48,390
I believe you.

536
00:32:48,390 --> 00:32:49,780
- Really? 
 - Really.

537
00:32:49,780 --> 00:32:51,630
Then say you believe me.

538
00:32:51,630 --> 00:32:54,820
I, Chen Huan Er, believe Jing Xi Chi will become a professional player

539
00:32:54,820 --> 00:32:57,320
for Real Madrid in the future.

540
00:32:57,320 --> 00:32:58,940
- You believe me? 
 - I do.

541
00:32:58,940 --> 00:33:02,750
It's good, because if you didn't...

542
00:33:12,400 --> 00:33:15,190
I have piano lessons, so I have to go.

543
00:33:17,960 --> 00:33:20,630
- Jing Xi Chi, you don't need to see me off. 
 - I'm not.

544
00:33:20,630 --> 00:33:22,320
I'm going there, too.

545
00:33:22,320 --> 00:33:24,880
- You want to learn musical instruments as well? 
 - No.

546
00:33:24,880 --> 00:33:27,890
I'm going to play football. The football field is over there.

547
00:33:27,890 --> 00:33:29,780
Sure.

548
00:33:34,780 --> 00:33:38,447
Qi Qi, what do you think of what I just said?

549
00:33:38,447 --> 00:33:39,530
What is it?

550
00:33:39,530 --> 00:33:42,330
The one about me going to Real Madrid.

551
00:33:44,600 --> 00:33:46,100
You don't believe me?

552
00:33:46,100 --> 00:33:47,600
I happen to have a game next week.

553
00:33:47,600 --> 00:33:49,430
Come have a look if you have time.

554
00:33:49,430 --> 00:33:53,130
I think I'll skip it. I don't know much about these.

555
00:33:53,130 --> 00:33:56,120
It's good that you have a hobby, but our main duty is to study.

556
00:33:56,120 --> 00:33:58,320
We still have to get good grades.

557
00:33:58,320 --> 00:33:59,743
I'm leaving. You don't have to walk with me. Bye.

558
00:33:59,743 --> 00:34:02,560
Come have a look if you have time.

559
00:34:07,230 --> 00:34:09,395
 Song Cong and Jing Xi Chi... 

560
00:34:09,395 --> 00:34:11,770
 One can't tell others his dream. 

561
00:34:11,770 --> 00:34:16,210
 The other one shared it but was dismissed as a childish fantasy. 

562
00:34:16,210 --> 00:34:20,210
 I don't know which is more frustrating. 

563
00:34:20,210 --> 00:34:23,080
 But I still envy them. 

564
00:34:23,080 --> 00:34:25,560
 At least they have goals. 

565
00:34:25,560 --> 00:34:29,650
 I don't even know where to go. 

566
00:34:30,440 --> 00:34:36,080
 I even used something as trivial as untied shoelaces as an excuse to just stand still. 

567
00:34:43,280 --> 00:34:46,620
Mom, how come you're back so soon?

568
00:34:46,620 --> 00:34:49,440
Why didn't you chat with Li Tian's mom longer?

569
00:34:49,440 --> 00:34:52,958
Isn't the position that Dad is aiming for this time quite important?

570
00:34:52,958 --> 00:34:55,180
Let your dad worry about it himself.

571
00:34:55,180 --> 00:34:58,370
If I stay any longer, I'll flip the table.

572
00:34:58,370 --> 00:35:00,174
You didn't see Li Tian's mom.

573
00:35:00,174 --> 00:35:03,083
When I told her you were taking TOEFL classes, her face turned green with envy.

574
00:35:03,083 --> 00:35:05,790
She's just jealous.

575
00:35:06,720 --> 00:35:10,200
I think you're a little too sensitive.

576
00:35:10,200 --> 00:35:11,830
I'm sensitive?

577
00:35:11,830 --> 00:35:15,120
Do you know how many years they've been talking about my low education level?

578
00:35:15,120 --> 00:35:20,220
What happened in the end? I still raised a child who's a top student.

579
00:35:21,060 --> 00:35:27,320
I also told them my son would only apply to the top five universities in the world.

580
00:35:27,320 --> 00:35:29,830
Here. Have some walnuts.

581
00:35:29,830 --> 00:35:33,830
I have to thank you. You really make our family proud.

582
00:35:35,780 --> 00:35:39,770
Mom, these walnuts were given to you. Eat them yourself.

583
00:35:39,770 --> 00:35:42,370
You usually work so hard.

584
00:35:42,370 --> 00:35:44,660
I'm not eating. You can eat them.

585
00:35:44,660 --> 00:35:46,370
You're my only child.

586
00:35:46,370 --> 00:35:48,520
You're our family's only hope.

587
00:35:48,520 --> 00:35:50,750
Eat more to supplement yourself.

588
00:35:54,660 --> 00:35:56,513
I'll continue studying, Mom.

589
00:35:56,513 --> 00:35:57,650
Take these.

590
00:35:57,650 --> 00:35:59,670
Finish them. Here.

591
00:36:23,960 --> 00:36:30,000
 Will such a planned life make you happy? 

592
00:36:42,360 --> 00:36:45,750
- You're home. 
 - Mom, I'm home.

593
00:36:49,350 --> 00:36:50,920
Mom.

594
00:36:50,920 --> 00:36:54,290
Did you get a promotion or a pay raise? You spent so much money.

595
00:36:54,290 --> 00:36:57,370
That's why I said you're dumb. You don't notice anything.

596
00:36:57,370 --> 00:36:59,670
Look who's back.

597
00:37:03,100 --> 00:37:06,060
Dad! Dad!

598
00:37:06,060 --> 00:37:08,550
My girl!

599
00:37:11,140 --> 00:37:13,250
I missed you so much.

600
00:37:13,250 --> 00:37:14,920
Dad, what's going on?

601
00:37:14,920 --> 00:37:16,800
You betrayed me. You didn't tell me in advance.

602
00:37:16,800 --> 00:37:18,300
I wanted to surprise you.

603
00:37:18,300 --> 00:37:21,570
Here, let me see if you've grown stronger.

604
00:37:22,810 --> 00:37:24,920
Good job. You kid...

605
00:37:24,920 --> 00:37:25,920
Grappling hand?

606
00:37:25,920 --> 00:37:27,820
How many times have I told you not to hurt her?

607
00:37:27,820 --> 00:37:30,620
You think I'll hurt her? She'll hurt me.

608
00:37:30,620 --> 00:37:33,440
Good job. I can tell you've been practicing a lot lately.

609
00:37:33,440 --> 00:37:34,720
But you guessed wrong.

610
00:37:34,720 --> 00:37:37,605
I've been so busy with my studies lately that I don't have time to practice.

611
00:37:37,605 --> 00:37:41,200
How can you be so proficient without any practice? Good job.

612
00:37:41,200 --> 00:37:42,545
There's so much meat, Mom.

613
00:37:42,545 --> 00:37:44,380
You've worked hard.

614
00:37:44,380 --> 00:37:45,677
Dad, don't you know?

615
00:37:45,677 --> 00:37:48,100
Mom rarely cooks this for me when you're not around.

616
00:37:48,100 --> 00:37:49,782
How dare you complain?

617
00:37:49,782 --> 00:37:52,380
Look at this seafood. This shrimp. I didn't even get this meat.

618
00:37:52,380 --> 00:37:54,470
Eat more.

619
00:37:54,470 --> 00:37:55,609
Eat more.

620
00:37:55,609 --> 00:37:57,359
I abused you.

621
00:37:57,359 --> 00:38:00,189
No. No.

622
00:38:00,189 --> 00:38:02,439
Come on. Hurry.

623
00:38:05,149 --> 00:38:07,799
The air today is really...

624
00:38:08,379 --> 00:38:11,149
Dad. Did you just fart?

625
00:38:11,149 --> 00:38:12,880
Mom, he farted.

626
00:38:12,880 --> 00:38:14,529
- That smell is from your mom! 
 - Cut it out.

627
00:38:14,529 --> 00:38:16,959
You ate too much corn.

628
00:38:18,669 --> 00:38:23,449
Dad, since you're also here, what do you want me to do in the future?

629
00:38:24,019 --> 00:38:27,500
Jing Xi Chi and Song Cong's families already have plans for them.

630
00:38:27,500 --> 00:38:30,019
I'm sure you have one for me, too, right?

631
00:38:30,019 --> 00:38:32,049
 No. 

632
00:38:33,800 --> 00:38:37,203
Huan Er, actually, you can do anything you want.

633
00:38:37,203 --> 00:38:39,499
- It's fine if you don't do anything. 
 - That's right.

634
00:38:39,499 --> 00:38:41,080
How can that work?

635
00:38:41,080 --> 00:38:42,549
Dad, Mom, let me tell you.

636
00:38:42,549 --> 00:38:47,149
Our classmates are all ambitious and have goals.

637
00:38:47,149 --> 00:38:51,520
Although we come from a small place, we must also have ambitions.

638
00:38:51,520 --> 00:38:53,320
Right?

639
00:38:53,939 --> 00:38:55,579
Ambitions?

640
00:38:58,749 --> 00:39:00,699
- Huan Er. 
 - Dad.

641
00:39:00,699 --> 00:39:04,279
Actually, you have plenty of time to think.

642
00:39:04,279 --> 00:39:06,499
- Yes. 
 - There's no rush.

643
00:39:06,499 --> 00:39:08,559
Take your time. Take one step at a time.

644
00:39:08,559 --> 00:39:10,379
- That's right. 
 - I get it, Mom.

645
00:39:10,379 --> 00:39:12,839
Aren't you talking about the tortoise and the hare?

646
00:39:12,839 --> 00:39:14,089
I'm the tortoise.

647
00:39:14,089 --> 00:39:16,009
I'll win in the end, right?

648
00:39:16,009 --> 00:39:17,499
Girlie.

649
00:39:17,499 --> 00:39:19,399
- Life is not a competition. 
 - Yes.

650
00:39:19,399 --> 00:39:21,269
Why do you have to win or lose?

651
00:39:21,269 --> 00:39:23,109
It's okay if we don't win, right?

652
00:39:23,109 --> 00:39:24,149
Yes.

653
00:39:24,149 --> 00:39:27,459
- We just hope you're healthy. 
 - Yes.

654
00:39:27,459 --> 00:39:29,460
Health and happiness are the most important.

655
00:39:29,460 --> 00:39:31,399
That's right.

656
00:39:31,399 --> 00:39:32,799
Dad, Mom, actually—

657
00:39:32,799 --> 00:39:35,399
Enough talking. You don't get it.

658
00:39:35,399 --> 00:39:36,939
Children nowadays are so tired.

659
00:39:36,939 --> 00:39:40,069
- Yeah. 
 - Why must there be a win or lose?

660
00:39:40,069 --> 00:39:41,759
It's not like how it used to be for us.

661
00:39:41,759 --> 00:39:43,399
You know, it used to be easy.

662
00:39:43,399 --> 00:39:47,029
Dad, Mom, your child's right here.

663
00:39:53,839 --> 00:39:58,919
If you can kick this bottle with every kick, you'll be close to being a professional.

664
00:39:59,419 --> 00:40:01,049
Come on.

665
00:40:09,419 --> 00:40:10,899
You're not even close.

666
00:40:10,899 --> 00:40:11,799
Again.

667
00:40:11,799 --> 00:40:13,109
It's fine.

668
00:40:13,109 --> 00:40:14,520
It's only my first kick.

669
00:40:14,520 --> 00:40:18,019
If I kick a thousand times, I'll definitely hit it.

670
00:40:21,589 --> 00:40:23,159
Again.

671
00:40:24,960 --> 00:40:26,440
That's enough from you.

672
00:40:26,440 --> 00:40:28,489
You're such a lousy player, yet you want to play professionally.

673
00:40:28,489 --> 00:40:29,609
Just treat it as a hobby.

674
00:40:29,609 --> 00:40:30,879
No, Dad. Let me try again.

675
00:40:30,879 --> 00:40:31,800
I'll give it another try.

676
00:40:31,800 --> 00:40:34,090
Listen. Use your thigh to bring out your calf.

677
00:40:34,090 --> 00:40:35,357
This is where you exert force.

678
00:40:35,357 --> 00:40:36,917
Let me try.

679
00:40:37,640 --> 00:40:42,020
♫  Wild roses in my hand  ♫

680
00:40:43,149 --> 00:40:46,459
Mr. Fu. I want to change classes.

681
00:40:48,520 --> 00:40:50,820
I wondered why you were deliberately 20 minutes late for the competition.

682
00:40:50,820 --> 00:40:53,009
So it was to lay the groundwork?

683
00:40:53,009 --> 00:40:55,399
There was a traffic jam that day.

684
00:40:56,019 --> 00:40:58,880
And I won a place in the competition.

685
00:40:58,880 --> 00:41:00,939
I just hope you can agree to let me change classes.

686
00:41:00,939 --> 00:41:03,619
Why do you have to change classes?

687
00:41:05,709 --> 00:41:07,589
I've made up my mind.

688
00:41:07,589 --> 00:41:09,579
I hope you'll agree.

689
00:41:11,800 --> 00:41:13,800
Thank you, Mr. Fu.

690
00:41:14,979 --> 00:41:16,649
This kid...

